				<p><p>It sounds like what you have is an <a href="http://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Occupancy_grid_mapping" rel="nofollow">occupancy grid</a>, which you could simply convert to a 2D array of booleans in memory. Your challenge will be to figure out what grid square you are in at any given time, and (when you are very confident about your location) mark down additional map obstacles as "occupied" on your map.</p>

<p>One way to figure out where you are over time is to use a <a href="http://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Particle_filter" rel="nofollow">particle filter</a>, and one way to find a path across an occupancy grid is to use <a href="http://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/A*_search_algorithm" rel="nofollow">the A* search</a>.</p>
